Package com.intellij.util.containers

Interface ConcurrentIntObjectMap<V>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IntObjectMap<V>

    public interface ConcurrentIntObjectMap<V>
extends IntObjectMap<V>
    Base interface for concurrent int key -> value:V map Null values are NOT allowed Methods are adapted from ConcurrentMap to integer keys
    See Also:
    ConcurrentMap

      • size

        int size()
        Specified by:
        size in interface IntObjectMap<V>
        Returns:
        Approximate number of elements in the map. The usage is discouraged since First, in concurrent context it doesn't have much sense and Second, for weak- or soft- keyed maps it returns the total number of references rather than alive values because otherwise it would be too expensive
